text: The Tudor House is an 18th-century house in Langport, Somerset, England. It was built in 1776 but had fallen into disrepair until it was bought and restored by the Somerset Buildings Preservation Trust in 1991 and is now a Grade II listed building. == References == == External links == * Tudor House, Langport from Somerset Buildings Preservation Trust Category:Country houses in Somerset Category:Houses completed in 1776 Category:Grade II listed buildings in South Somerset Category:Langport
